e they live in:\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-8-\ndocs/workflows.md:9:**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) — Run inside a Docker\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-10-container via `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type. These are the\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-11-standard workflows for coding tasks.\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-12-\ndocs/workflows.md:13:**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) — Runs on the host machine as the daemon\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-14-process. Steps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow` step type\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-15-dispatches a container workflow run and waits for it to complete. This is the extension\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-16-point for custom orchestration strategies.\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-17-\ndocs/workflows.md-18-The convention is enforced at parse time: a `workflow_name` step in a container workflow\n--\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-39-\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-40-**script** (has `run`) — Runs a shell command. Used for tests, linters, validators, or\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-41-any deterministic check. Available in both host and container workflows.\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-42-\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-43-**workflow** (has `workflow_name`) — Dispatches a named container workflow run and blocks\ndocs/workflows.md:44:until it completes. Only available in host workflows (`host.cloche`).\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-45-\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-46-A step with more than one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`, or none of them, is a\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-47-parse error.\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-48-\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-49-## DSL Syntax\n--\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-133-wires to different steps without conflict.\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-134-\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-135-## Host Workflow Example\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-136-\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-137-```\ndocs/workflows.md:138:# .cloche/host.cloche — runs on the host machine\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-139-workflow \"main\" {\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-140-  step prepare-prompt {\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-141-    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-142-    results = [success, fail]\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-143-  }\n--\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md-3-**Date:** 2026-03-06\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md-4-**Status:** Design\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md-5-\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md-6-## Problem\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md-7-\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md:8:`cloche init` is out of date. It does not create `config.toml`, `host.cloche`,\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md-9-`scripts/`, or `version`. Its `.gitignore` strategy inverts the right default: it\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md-10-ignores `.cloche/*/` then negates specific subdirectories, which means any new\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md-11-directory added to `.cloche/` is accidentally ignored until explicitly whitelisted.\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md-12-\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md-13-## New `.gitignore` strategy\n--\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md-50-```\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md-51-.cloche/\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md-52-  config.toml          # project settings (new)\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md-53-  version              # project version counter, content: \"1\" (new)\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md-54-  <workflow>.cloche    # container workflow definition (existing)\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md:55:  host.cloche          # host orchestration workflow (new)\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-0