-design.md-25-### File location\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-26-\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-27-```\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md:28:.cloche/host.cloche\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-29-```\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-30-\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-31-If the file does not exist, the daemon falls back to the current hard-coded behavior\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-32-(pull task → LLM prompt generation → dispatch container workflow).\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-33-\n--\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-115-    Dispatch  RunDispatcher      / existing: dispatches a container workflow run\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-116-    WaitRun   RunWaiter          / new: blocks until a run ID completes, returns final state\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-117-    AgentCmd  string             // command to invoke for prompt steps on host\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-118-}\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-119-\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md:120:// RunWorkflow executes the named workflow from a parsed host.cloche Workflow\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-121-// for a single task. Returns the final result (\"done\" or \"abort\").\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-122-func (r *HostRunner) RunWorkflow(ctx context.Context, wf *domain.Workflow, task ports.Task, orchRunID string) (string, error)\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-123-```\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-124-\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-125-Step execution:\n--\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-157-2. Claim task\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-158-3. Call `promptGen.Generate(task)`\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-159-4. Call `dispatch(workflow, projectDir, prompt)` → runID\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-160-5. (In-flight counter managed, `OnRunComplete` decrements it)\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-161-\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md:162:**New flow (when `host.cloche` exists):**\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-163-1. Pull ready tasks\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-164-2. Claim task\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md:165:3. Parse `.cloche/host.cloche` → find `main` workflow\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-166-4. Generate an `orchRunID` (`main-<namegen>`)\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-167-5. Spin up a goroutine: call `hostRunner.RunWorkflow(ctx, orch wf, task, orchRunID)`\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-168-6. On goroutine return: decrement in-flight, update task state (success/fail)\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-169-\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-170-The old `promptGen` and `dispatch` are still used as the **fallback** when\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md:171:`host.cloche` is absent (no breaking change for existing projects).\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-172-\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-173-`WaitRun` needs access to the run store. Wire it in `initOrchestrator` in\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-174-`cmd/cloched/main.go`.\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-175-\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-176----\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md-177-\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md:178:## Default `host.cloche` (from `cloche init`)\n/workspa