[2026-03-09T23:15:34Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DZiHosftgvSsQZZanaogQN","type":"tool_result","content":"   175→\n   176→---\n   177→\n   178→## Default `host.cloche` (from `cloche init`)\n   179→\n   180→```\n   181→# host.cloche — orchestration workflow (runs on host, not in container)\n   182→# Steps here execute as the daemon user. Keep operations simple and safe.\n   183→\n   184→workflow \"main\" {\n   185→  step prepare-prompt {\n   186→    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n   187→    results = [success, fail]\n   188→  }\n   189→\n   190→  step develop {\n   191→    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n   192→    results       = [success, fail]\n   193→  }\n   194→\n   195→  prepare-prompt:success -> develop\n   196→  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n   197→  develop:success        -> done\n   198→  develop:fail           -> done\n   199→}\n   200→```\n   201→\n   202→And `.cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh` (created by init, chmod +x):\n   203→\n   204→```bash\n   205→#!/usr/bin/env bash\n   206→# Default prompt generator. Uses task env vars injected by cloched.\n   207→# Write the prompt to $CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT (also echoed to stdout).\n   208→set -euo pipefail\n   209→\n   210→prompt=\"## Task: ${CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE}\n   211→\n   212→${CLOCHE_TASK_BODY}\"\n   213→\n   214→echo \"$prompt\"\n   215→[ -n \"${CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT:-}\" ] && echo \"$prompt\" > \"$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT\"\n   216→```\n   217→\n   218→---\n   219→\n   220→## `.gitignore` update\n   221→\n   222→`cloche init` adds `.cloche/scripts/` is NOT gitignored (scripts are project config).\n   223→The orchestration run output dirs follow the same pattern as container run dirs:\n   224→`.cloche/main-*/` is gitignored via the existing `.cloche/*/` rule."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3fb2401a-6b6a-4fd9-9eca-7aeee6bcc4bd","uuid":"48daddcc-0e9e-4267-ae60-22c53dd751ac","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md","content":"\n---\n\n## Default `host.cloche` (from `cloche init`)\n\n```\n# host.cloche — orchestration workflow (runs on host, not in container)\n# Steps here execute as the daemon user. Keep operations simple and safe.\n\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  step prepare-prompt {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step develop {\n    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n    results       = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  prepare-prompt:success -> develop\n  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n  develop:success        -> done\n  develop:fail           -> done\n}\n```\n\nAnd `.cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh` (created by init, chmod +x):\n\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Default prompt generator. Uses task env vars injected by cloched.\n# Write the prompt to $CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT (also echoed to stdout).\nset -euo pipefail\n\nprompt=\"## Task: ${CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE}\n\n${CLOCHE_TASK_BODY}\"\n\necho \"$prompt\"\n[ -n \"${CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT:-}\" ] && echo \"$prompt\" > \"$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## `.gitignore` update\n\n`cloche init` adds `.cloche/scripts/` is NOT gitignored (scripts are project config).\nThe orchestration run output dirs follow the same pattern as container run dirs:\n`.cloche/main-*/` is gitignored via the existing `.cloche/*/` rule.","numLines":50,"startLine":175,"totalLines":249}}}
